Revision history for JCVI-Bounds

0.3.0   Apr 21 2009
  - Moved common functions to JCVI::Bounds::Interface

0.2.4   Apr 17 2009
  - Fixed bug in Bounds::e53 where end5 == end3
  - Suppressed warnings in Set::strand

0.2.3   Apr 16 2009
  - Added intersection to Bounds
  - Added bounds method to Set
  - Cleaned up inheritance from Bounds in Set

0.2.2   Apr 15 2009
  - Added JCVI::Bounds::Set
  - Polished documentation in Bounds

0.2.1   Apr 15 2009
  - Put use version on same line as $VERSION declared
  - Added META.yml so make dist would work

0.2.0   Apr 15 2009
  - Moved to JCVI::Bounds
  - Implemented as an arrayref with just 3 values
  - Quicker than using Class::Accessor::Validing
  - Meant to be used with composition (i.e. your object has a bounds object)

0.1.0
  - Initial version
  - Based on Class::Accessor::Validating
  - Was meant to be extended